e key array and filters only the checked objects for deletion. I'm iterating through the users array, constructing composite keys from each user's ID and primary key fields, then checking if those keys exist in the deleted composite keys list to filter out the users that should be removed. The StringBuilder code appears to be unused—it's created but never actually applied anywhere, so removing it was the right call. Looking back at the source introduction, it references another document and explains the use case for handling partial selections in lists with composite keys, which the knowledge file already captures adequately in the summary section.\n\nI'm confident the knowledge file is solid overall. The section count warning is just a false positive from the document title being counted as a heading. Checking the s3 section more carefully, the source mentions a hyperlink to an external reference about script tags, but the knowledge file correctly conveys the core constraint—that a specific script tag must be used—without needing to preserve the link itself. The official_doc_urls field being empty seems appropriate here since there's no external documentation being referenced. I'm satisfied the knowledge file is accurate and complete—the relative documentation link doesn't need to be included in official_doc_urls since it can't be resolved to an absolute URL.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17802,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":17802,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74fd8605-8adf-4a23-8239-ac3c5625c8a1","uuid":"54664322-3d5d-4316-af5f-ace5af940092"}
